  </subsection>
  
  <subsection>
    <title>Horizontal Translation</title>

    <definition xml:id="def-horizontal_translation">
      <title>Horizontal Translation</title>
      <statement>
	<p>
	  Let <m>c</m> be a positive number.
	  We say the function <m>g(x)</m> is a <term>horizontal translation</term>
	  <idx>
	    <h>Graph</h>
	    <h>Tranformation</h>
	    <h>Translation Horizontal</h>
	  </idx>
	  of the function <m>f(x)</m> if <m>g(x) = f(x \pm c)</m>.
	  <ul>
	    <li>
	      <p>
		The graph of <m>g(x) = f(x - c)</m> is obtained by shifting the graph of <m>y = f(x)</m> to the right along the <m>x</m>-axis by <m>c</m> units.
	      </p>
	    </li>
	    <li>
	      <p>
		The graph of <m>g(x) = f(x + c)</m> is obtained by shifting the graph of <m>y = f(x)</m> to the left along the <m>x</m>-axis by <m>c</m>-units.
	      </p>
	    </li>
	  </ul>
	</p>
      </statement>
    </definition>

    <example component="web">
      <statement>
	<p>
	  Use <xref ref="fig-parabola" text="custom">the graph of <m>y = x^2</m></xref> to graph the functions <m>g(x) = (x+2)^2</m> and <m>h(x) = (x-3)^2</m>.
	</p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
	<p>
	  The graph of <m>g(x)</m> is obtained by translating the graph of <m>f(x)</m> to the left along the <m>x</m>-axis by <m>2</m> units, and the graph of <m>h(x)</m> is obtained by translating the graph of <m>f(x)</m> to the right along the <m>x</m>-axis by 3 units.
	</p>
	<figure xml:id="fig-example_horiz_translate">
	  <caption>Horizontal translation of <m>y = f(x)</m> to the left by <m>2</m> and to the right by <m>3</m></caption>
	  <image xml:id="img-example_horiz_translate">
	    <latex-image xml:id="tikz-example_horiz_translate">
	      <xi:include parse="text" href="tex/transformations/horizontal_translation.tex"/>
	    </latex-image>
	  </image>
	</figure>
      </solution>
    </example>

