  <subsection>
    <title>Reflection</title>

    <definition xml:id="def-reflection">
      <title>Reflection</title>
      <statement>
	<p>
	  We say the function <m>g(x)</m> is a <term>reflection</term>
	  <idx>
	    <h>Graph</h>
	    <h>Tranformation</h>
	    <h>Reflection</h>
	  </idx>
	  of <m>f(x)</m> if either <m>g(x) = -f(x)</m> or <m>g(x) = f(-x).</m>
	  <ul>
	    <li>
	      <p>
		The graph of <m>g(x) = -f(x)</m> is obtained by reflecting the graph of <m>y = f(x)</m> over the <m>x</m>-axis.
	      </p>
	    </li>
	    <li>
	      <p>
		The graph of <m>g(x) = f(-x)</m> is obtained by reflecting the graph of <m>y = f(x)</m> over the <m>y</m>-axis.
	      </p>
	    </li>
	  </ul>
	</p>
      </statement>
    </definition>

    <example component="web">
      <statement>
	<p>
	  Use <xref ref="fig-sq_root" text="custom">the graph of <m>y = \sqrt{x}</m></xref> to graph the functions <m>g(x) = -\sqrt{x}</m> and <m>h(x) = \sqrt{-x}</m>.
	</p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
	<p>
	  The graph of <m>g(x)</m> is obtained by reflecting the graph of <m>f(x)</m> over the <m>x</m>-axis, and the graph of <m>h(x)</m> is obtained by reflecting the graph of <m>f(x)</m> over the <m>y</m>-axis.
	</p>
	<figure xml:id="fig-example_reflection">
	  <caption>Reflection of <m>y = f(x)</m> across the <m>x</m>-axis and <m>y</m>-axis.</caption>
	  <image xml:id="img-example_reflection">
		 <latex-image xml:id="tikz-example_reflection">
	      <xi:include parse="text" href="tex/transformations/reflections.tex"/>
	    </latex-image>
	  </image>
	</figure>
      </solution>
    </example>

